#What are the builders

The builders in marscss are responsible for generating CSS rules for our application, there are different builders to generate helpers, generate class to work with columns, css reset, etc...

As we have seen in the <%= link_to 'introduction of marscss', '/documentation' %>, the organization of loading marscss is very important, in the load scheme of css the builders are loaded in the last position, after of custom core.

* core marscss
* custom variables
* custom core
* builders marscss

##Basic example

As we can see in the following example, this would be a normal load of marscss.

At the end of the `scss` you will see that there is a builder added, in this case` mars-build-reset` which is responsible for adding the generic marscss reset rules

As we can see in the result `css` auto generate the different rules set in that builder

